Package: stppSim
Type: Package
Title: Spatial and Temporal Point Patterns Simulation for Social Science Research
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Monsuru Adepeju [cre, aut], 
  Meng Le Zhang [aut]
Maintainer: Monsuru Adepeju <monsuur2010@yahoo.com>
Description: Generates artificial spatio-temporal point patterns (stpp) through the 
  integration of microsimulation and agent-based models. Allows a user to 
  define the behavioural properties of a "walker" on a spatially configured
  landscape in order to simulates point events over time. The resulting
  spatiotemporal signatures of output data can be assessed .Package showcases examples
  of ways by which the st model evaluation and testi.
  The proposed idea (of a 'walker') is applicable in domains such as Criminology
  (e.g. offender), Zoology (e.g. foraging animal), and 
  epidemiology (e.g. carrier). Functions are included for simulation for stpp from
  scratch and from a sparse version of a real-life data.
  This chapter showcases examples of ways by which the package ca
  n be utilized in criminological research for spati
  otemporal model testing and evaluation.
